  "84th Radar Evaluation Squadron (RADES) radar data analysis for the FBI, 13 Sep 2001 (FOIA release): per-sweep radar returns with computed lat/lon, Mode C altitude, and Mode 3 beacon code",
  "9/11 Commission interview of Lt. Col. Steven O'Brien, USAF 133rd Airlift Wing (Minnesota Air National Guard), archives.gov declassified ISCAP 2011-048-doc22",
  "9/11 Commission Report, Ch. 1 notes - the C-130H asked by Washington control to identify and follow AA77, then near the UA93 crash site"
 ],
 "provenance_notes": [
  "RADAR-SURVEYED TRACK: 284 of 285 waypoints are 84 RADES radar returns (sites PLA; ~12 s antenna sweep), extracted by analysis/extract_rades_notables.py. Cross-site registration bias is corrected toward the primary site; garbled plots are speed-filtered. The remaining 1 waypoints are documented anchors (takeoff runway, coverage-gap positions, impact point).",
  "ALTITUDE: alt_src='modec' waypoints carry the transponder's Mode C pressure altitude (100 ft quanta); alt_src='interp' waypoints (transponder off) interpolate through the documented NTSB profile anchors; alt_src='anchor' are the documented anchors themselves.",
  "TAKEOFF ANCHOR APPROXIMATION: the Andrews AFB runway anchor at 13:31:00Z is placed ~90 s before the first radar return (13:32:26Z, 300 ft Mode C in the climb-out); O'Brien reported taking off 'about 09:30' ET. NO IMPACT: the aircraft did not crash \u2014 the track simply ends at the last RADES return (14:29:20Z) as it leaves the analyzed coverage, en route Minneapolis-St. Paul."
 ],
